features: 【⌨ 3-Level Height Adjustment】Yikola desk accessories set creatively combines tilted clear acrylic keyboard holder with wrist rest for optimal viewing and minimum wrist fatigue. This ergonomic wrist rest features 3 different height levels (0 cm /1 cm /2 cm) to keep keyboard at your desired tilt angle.

【⌨ PU Leather with Breather Holes Design】The wrist pad adopts high-quality smooth PU Leather with small perforations on the surface to allow air flow and enhance the comfort during long time of typing or gaming.

【⌨ Non-slip &Safe Keyboard Riser】Unlike traditional lip stoppers on each end that may interfere or stab your hands, our rectangular wrist rest has the same width as the acrylic keyboard lift to fully avoid your keyboard from sliding down and wobbly. Rounded edge design protects potential damage to your hands.

【⌨ Perfectly Fit Various Keyboard】The top surface of this keyboard lift measures 16.9 inches wide and 7.28 inches deep, making it compatible with almost all kinds of thin keyboard, magic keyboard, mini keyboard, full-sized keyboard, etc. Slot on the back of keyboard stand for neatly organizing your cables and wires.

【⌨ Wide Space for Storage & Display】The spacious design also promises plenty of space underneath to store your full-sized keyboard and remain dust-free when not in use. Clear acrylic material also beautifully displays your multi-color keyboard.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Modern and Clean Style Included with Comfort
reviews.reviewText: I got this because my wrists remind me how slim and flat the Apple Magic Keyboard every evening as they pulse with discomfort from daily use. I was hoping it would provide me a better angle to use my keyboard, raise my hands so that my wrists are not resting on the hard corner of the edge of my desk all day and possibly provide me some extra desk space with the are beneath it being available to slide devices not currently being used beneath it. It definitely lifts my wrists off the edge and the cushion is waaaay more comfortable than the desk itself and I feel like the angle of my keyboard is much better suited for use with how wrists are naturally intended to bend, but since I have to use the thicker side of the cushion for that angle, the thinner portion of it blocks a lot of the storage area beneath and I wasn’t able to fit most of the items I had hoped I could beneath it. That said, it fulfills its intended use perfectly and for just under $20 you can’t beat the price compared to other options. I was worried sleek black acrylic would scuff easily and look cheap, but the cushion keeps your hands from gliding across it and it maintains a nice, polished and sleek look that fits perfectly with the carbon fiber and tech aesthetic of my desk. All in all I’d recommend this to anyone in need of an affordable, simple and easy to use keyboard riser. Terrific product!
